				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To add to the ongoing CHA debate.  The whole debate seems kind of pointless.  Have a peak at Velious quest armour of any kind..hey lookie..has cha.  Oh and planar gear? same thing.  ANY enchanter specific armour has CHA on it as well as INT...often MORE CHA.  So explain to me why VI puts CHA on chanter gear if it's not important.<BR>
<BR>
AFter over 2 years of playing the class, I can personally say if your cha sucks dont' bother doing CC.  You will be a mana drain on the cleric, and odds are you will die.  Strive to have both your cha and Int at 255.  Look for +mana, and +HP items too.  HP are important.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway that's my two cents. if you want to see what stats are important...look at the freaking gear VI designed. <BR>
<BR>
Xaeviouran Orionne<BR>
