				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Oh, I feel dumber just for reading this page.  If you are an enchanter, what do you do?  Crowd Control. CROWD CONTROL!  You need CHA, it affects the length of your mez and charms!  INT is secondary, and you should pump it up too, but CHA is your main stat.  Plus Enchanters get the Clarity line of spells.  The only freaking mana regen spell in the game, only bards get another form of it in a song.  This means your mana will recover, as will all of your party members, and you wont worry about being oom so much, and can continuously cast mez, then sit and med, and when it fades, mez again.  Charming isnt that helpful unless you are in a place where trains seem to wreak havoc, then use it, or you are soloing, which is suicide without charms.  That brings it back around to where CHA is needed, mez and charm length, what happens if your charm fades in the middle of a fight, hmm?  Dead enchanter, cuz now you got 2 mobs, you're mez keeps getting interupted, you get stunned every time you are unstunned, and now you wish you hadnt hasted that charmed mob.  In conclusion: WE CHANTERS NEED CHA FIRST AND FOREMOST, then get your int up.<BR>
<BR>
I hope some of you will get this through your thick skulls.<BR>
